channel_description: Watch Ash and Goh’s adventures in Pokémon Master Journeys: The Series on Pokémon TV.

media.description: As Chloe takes her time deciding whether to become a Pokémon Trainer, it turns out her decision is right in front of her!
media.title: To Train, or Not to Train!

media.description: Ash and Goh have always been fascinated with all kinds of Pokémon, and now Chloe is joining them on their latest adventure!
media.title: A Pinch of This, a Pinch of That!

media.description: Ash wants to improve his World Coronation Series ranking, and there’s only one way to do it: by battling!
media.title: Trials of a Budding Master!

media.description: A visit to a vegetable farm has our heroes researching Pokémon in a most surprising way!
media.title: How Are You Gonna Keep ‘Em Off of the Farm?

media.description: A Legendary Pokémon is in trouble, and our heroes are there to help as best as they can!
media.title: Healing the Healer!

media.description: When our heroes visit a movie set, Sobble’s outlook on battling undergoes a transformation!
media.title: Sobble Spies A Stealthy Strategy!

media.description: A fascinating book inspires Chloe to take on an equally fascinating mission!
media.title: The Tale of You and Glimwood Tangle!

media.description: Ash and Farfetch’d want to hone their leek-wielding skills, and there’s a place in Kalos where they can do just that!
media.title: Searching for Chivalry!

media.description: A snowy day provides an opportunity to relive fond memories and forge new ones, too!
media.title: Memories of A Warming Kindness!

media.description: There are always plenty of adventures to go around: for people and Pokémon!
media.title: A Rollicking Roll… Eyes on the Goal!

media.description: Goh finds a Grookey who’s been separated from its Trainer, but things are not as simple as they seem!
media.title: When a House is Not a Home!

media.description: Ash is working hard to reach his goal of battling Leon, so it’s time for another World Coronation Series match!
media.title: Beyond Chivalry… Aiming to be a Leek Master!

media.description: Ash and Goh meet some workers in need of assistance, so they jump right in and help!
media.title: Searching for Service with a Smile!

media.description: An unexpected Evolution brings back an unexpected memory for Goh!
media.title: Not Too Close for Comfort!

media.description: A meeting with a Vaporeon Trainer has Chloe thinking about Eevee’s future!
media.title: On Land, In the Sea, and to the Future!

media.description: A request from a friend has our heroes off to save the day!
media.title: Absol Absolved!

media.description: An invitation from an old friend has Ash really excited and looking toward the Pokémon World Coronation Series with renewed determination!
media.title: Thrash of the Titans!

media.description: Our heroes are on a mission to help a diminutive Pokémon in distress!
media.title: Under Color of Darkness!

media.description: A rash of wrongdoing is gripping Vermilion City, but our heroes are there to crack the case!
media.title: Sleuths for Truth!

media.description: Goh has a big decision to make, and Ash’s first rival is here to help!
media.title: Advice to Goh!

media.description: When Grookey and Eevee run their first errand, it becomes a learning experience for everyone!
media.title: Errand Endurance!

media.description: Team Rocket has a big decision to make, and their food supply depends on it!
media.title: Take My Thief! Please!

media.description: Goh’s first test for Project Mew awaits—along with some very challenging situations!
media.title: Leaping Toward the Dream!

media.description: Unexpected alliances form when our heroes and Team Rocket get mixed up underground!
media.title: Everybody’s Doing the Underground Shuffle!

media.description: A trip to the Galar region has Ash and Goh doing some surprising research about Pokémon teamwork!
media.title: Grabbing the Brass Ring!

media.description: A series of mysterious events are occurring in Sinnoh, so our heroes are off to investigate!
media.title: Nightfall? Nightmares!

media.description: A legendary conflict unfolds as our heroes investigate the source of nightmares in the Sinnoh region!
media.title: A Midsummer Night's Light!

media.description: When Ash and Goh enter a race in Alola, the other competitors go all out to make it a challenge!
media.title: All Out, All of the Time!

media.description: Cerise Laboratory’s research data has been deleted, and everyone is determined to find out why!
media.title: Detective Drizzile!

media.description: An encounter with some remarkable people and Pokémon gives Chloe and Eevee some valuable life lessons!
media.title: Night and Day, You are the Ones!

media.description: Goh’s first trial mission for Project Mew is about to begin, and it promises to deliver a host of surprises!
media.title: Trial on a Golden Scale!

media.description: After Goh catches a rare Pokémon, our heroes meet some unusual people with some fascinating, blue interests!
media.title: Mad About Blue!

media.description: Our heroes take on a challenge that gives the word “sweet” new meaning!
media.title: The Sweet Taste of Battle!

media.description: Ash and Goh visit a town in a difficult situation involving the difference between night and day!
media.title: Star Night, Star Flight!

media.description: Korrina and Gurkinn take our heroes to Mega Island, where Ash and Lucario face an unexpected test!
media.title: An Adventure of Mega Proportions!

media.description: Determined to advance in the World Coronation Series, Ash and Bea battle in the Ultra Class!
media.title: Battle Three With Bea!

media.description: Ash’s battle against Bea develops into a full-throttled competition where the victor is anyone’s guess!
media.title: A Battle of Mega Versus Max!

media.description: A new classmate at Chloe and Goh’s school has a Glaceon with an icy disposition!
media.title: Breaking the Ice!

media.description: Continuing his quest to join Project Mew, Goh faces his second trial mission!
media.title: Looking out for Number Two!

media.description: A mysterious phenomenon pulls our heroes into uncharted territory!
media.title: The Gates of Warp!

media.description: Confronted with an unexpected reality, our heroes team up with some unexpected allies!
media.title: Showdown at the Gates of Warp!

channel_description: Ash and his friends love catching z’s, and Pokémon, on Pokémon TV.

media.description: On empty stomachs, our heroes' search for food brings them to a small village, but find there is no food at the bakery nor at the grocery store; even the town restaurant is out of food.
media.title: Wake Up Snorlax!

media.description: Our heroes trudge along, resigning themselves to the idea of camping out in the desert as the sun slowly sets. Suddenly they see bright lights in front of them: a glamorous city appears before them, covered in neon lights.
media.title: The Song of Jigglypuff

media.description: Ash uses Corphish in his Gym battle with Flannery. Flannery chooses Magcargo first, which is defeated by Corphish's Crabhammer.
media.title: Going, Going, Yawn

media.description: The kids have stopped by the Banana Slakoth Garden on their way to Lilycove City, but the gate is closed and the trees have no fruit on them.
media.title: The Garden of Eatin'

media.description: Ash discovers that his opponent, Gym Leader Cilan, is a kindred spirit!
media.title: Dreams by the Yard Full!

media.description: Visiting a seemingly lifeless part of Capacia Island, our heroes come upon a life-giving solution to its problem!
media.title: Searching For a Wish!

media.description: A nighttime campout brings some interesting adventures for our heroes’ Pokémon!
media.title: Dream a Little Dream from Me!

media.description: A Pokémon School camping trip, complete with a scary campfire story, makes for an experience our heroes will never forget!
media.title: Lulled to La-La Land!

media.description: A sleepover at Professor Kukui’s house sets the stage for fun, friendship, and unexpected adventure!
media.title: Night of a Thousand Poses!

media.description: Our heroes are wondering about Komala’s sleep patterns when they’re interrupted by a familiar visitor!
media.title: Let Sleeping Pokémon Lie!

channel_description: From heartwarming to silly, the POKÉTOON series of animated shorts has Pokémon fun for all moods!

media.description: On the hunt for some tasty Poké Beans, Scraggy runs into a peculiar Pokémon—Mimikyu! Mimikyu wants to be friends, but Scraggy only wants snacks. Watch as they chase each other toward a potential friendship.
media.title: Scraggy and Mimikyu

media.description: Pancham dreams of becoming a hero, so it trains every day. When some people and Pokémon are in trouble, does Pancham have what it takes to be the hero they need?
media.title: The Pancham Who Wants to Be a Hero

media.description: Blossom’s goal is to become a Pokémon League Champion! During a trip into the forest, she has a chance encounter with a Pokémon who will test her dreams.
media.title: Blossom’s Dream

media.description: A loyal Magikarp wants nothing more than to make a friend.
media.title: Wait for Me, Magikarp!

media.description: Spend a cozy, snowy day in a house full of friendly Pokémon.
media.title: The Slugma-Powered Home

media.description: Afterschool activities get more interesting when a mysterious Gengar stirs up some fun.
media.title: Help! I’ve Turned into a Gengar

media.description: A hot summer day suddenly turns into a snowy wonderland for three friends. Could a Pokémon have something to do with it?
media.title: Snorunt’s Summer Vacation

media.description: Jigglypuff is sad because its song isn’t like the songs of other Jigglypuff. Will it be able to find the right melody with a friend’s help?
media.title: Jigglypuff’s Song

channel_description: A young boy befriends a Hisuian Zorua despite his father’s wishes in Pokémon: Hisuian Snow. Watch the limited animated series now!

media.description: Alec returns to the Hisui region to visit his father. There, he recalls events from his childhood when he encountered a wild Pokémon in a snow-covered forest...
media.title: Onto the Icy Blue

media.description: After falling down a cliffside, young Alec befriends the Hisuian Zorua, and they work together to climb back up. But when Alec returns to his father, he's surprised at his father's reaction upon seeing the Zorua.
media.title: Fiery Reflections in Snow

media.description: After many years, Alec returns to the Hisui region to collect the medicinal plants he learned about as a child...and maybe see an old friend.
media.title: Two Hues

channel_description: Watch the limited series to take a bold new look at the people and Pokémon of the many regions of the Pokémon world.

media.description: What goes through the mind of a Pokémon Champion as they prepare to face the greatest challenge of all? Doubts? Regrets? Determination? All three?
media.title: Episode 1: The Champion

media.description: As the sun sets on some painful memories, Lillie vows to rescue her mother and bring back her friend Nebby. But, in her moment of triumph, a sinister presence casts a shadow on their moonlit reunion…
media.title: Episode 2: The Eclipse

media.description: What do you do when everyone tells you you’re wrong for what you think? Do you stop and listen? Or do you follow your vision no matter the cost, even if it risks the people and Pokémon of Kalos?
media.title: Episode 3: The Visionary

media.description: He thought of everything as he plotted and schemed behind the scenes. He manipulated people and Pokémon as each piece of his plan for Unova fell into place exactly as intended.
media.title: Episode 4: The Plan

media.description: Rivals. No matter how fast you run through Sinnoh, they’re always one step ahead, driving you to be better. But at some point, whoever they are, you must stop to face them and their Pokémon.
media.title: Episode 5: The Rival

media.description: All her life, she’s been told the story of her people, bound to their wishes and to her duty to Hoenn. Lorekeeper Zinnia has always known what she has to do…but when the Legendary Pokémon Rayquaza arrives, will she have what it takes?
media.title: Episode 6: The Wish

media.description: We raise the curtain on the Kimono Girls as they perform a tale of the Legendary Pokémon of Johto in a magical storytelling experience you’ll never forget!
media.title: Episode 7: The Show

media.description: It started as a whisper that became a rumor. Now everyone is talking about it—the most powerful Pokémon ever has been discovered in Kanto! And Green, Pokémon Trainer extraordinaire, is racing to catch it. But she’s not the only one....
media.title: Episode 8: The Discovery

channel_description: Look out! Bidoof bumbles into trouble in the new animated short Bidoof’s Big Stand. Catch the adventure now!

media.description: A bumbling Bidoof with a tendency to bite off more than it can chew finds itself between a rock and a hard place as it embarks on a journey to find its place in the world.
media.title: Bidoof's Big Stand

channel_description: Leon visits the Isle of Armor in The Gathering of Stars, a special new episode of Pokémon: Twilight Wings, now on Pokémon TV!

media.description: The initial chapter of the new seven-episode animated series set in the Galar region is now available for you to enjoy.
media.title: Episode 1: Letter

media.description: After losing to Galar’s Champion, Leon, Fighting-type Gym Leader Bea sets out with her Pokémon to elevate their training. Will she find her inner resolve and grow stronger, or will she succumb to the pressure of defeat?
media.title: Episode 2: Training

media.description: Hop idolizes his older brother, Leon, who along with his partner Pokémon, Charizard, have earned the title of Champion. Wooloo, Hop’s partner Pokémon, is jealous of the admiration shown for Leon’s Charizard and decides to prove that it’s also worthy of the Champion title.
media.title: Episode 3: Buddy

media.description: Nessa, an incredibly popular Gym Leader and model, has always strived to be the best. Her focus is split between the two professions, and Chairman Rose advises her to choose one path or the other if she truly wants to be number one. Will she sacrifice one dream in pursuit of the other?
media.title: Episode 4: Early-Evening Waves

media.description: There’s never a moment’s rest for Oleana as she solves problems big and small to keep Galar running smoothly. But sometimes a break puts everything back in perspective and reminds us why we do what we do.
media.title: Episode 5: Assistant

media.description: After getting into an argument with his friend John, Tommy wants to make amends. He enlists Allister, Galar’s Ghost-type Gym Leader, to help in a most unusual way.
media.title: Episode 6: Moonlight

media.description: The day of Leon’s Championship match has arrived, and thanks to John’s letter, all the kids at the hospital are invited to attend! But in his excitement, John oversleeps and almost misses his chance to go to the stadium. Will he be able to make it to the battle in time?
media.title: Episode 7: Sky

media.description: Leon heads to the Isle of Armor to meet with his former mentor, Mustard, and ask for his support. By gathering star Trainers from across Galar, he’ll create a tournament unlike any other!
media.title: Pokémon: Twilight Wings—The Gathering of Stars

channel_description: Ash and Pikachu’s exciting adventures continue with new friends and new Pokémon! Watch Pokémon Journeys: The Series on Pokémon TV today!

media.description: A series of past events set the stage for the friendships and adventures of the present!
media.title: Enter Pikachu!

media.description: A visit to a brand-new research laboratory puts Ash on a path to meet a kindred spirit!
media.title: Legend? Go! Friends? Go!

media.description: As Ash and Goh become accustomed to their new roles as research fellows for Professor Cerise, they find themselves surrounded by Pokémon mystery and wonder!
media.title: Ivysaur’s Mysterious Tower!

media.description: Ash and Goh visit the Galar region and meet a small Pokémon with a big heart!
media.title: Settling the Scorbunny!

media.description: Ash and Goh search the Wild Area for giant Pokémon, and a little friend wants to join them!
media.title: Mind-Boggling Dynamax!

media.description: With Scorbunny by his side, Goh decides on a new goal—catch every kind of Pokémon!
media.title: Working My Way Back to Mew!

media.description: Goh’s ambition may be to catch as many Pokémon as possible, but Ash wants to put some serious battling into the mix!
media.title: Serving Up the Flute Cup!

media.description: As Ash and Goh pursue their goals, they meet an exceptionally driven Pokémon with a big ambition of its own!
media.title: The Sinnoh Iceberg Race!

media.description: When our heroes set off to investigate a rumor, finding a Legendary Pokémon becomes top priority!
media.title: Finding a Legend!

media.description: Ash and Goh set out to find a special island spoken of in rumors—what kind of discoveries will they make?
media.title: A Test in Paradise!

media.description: An encounter with a frightening opponent gets resolved by a Pokémon who’s anything but frightening!
media.title: Best Friend...Worst Nightmare!

media.description: Thanks to Professor Cerise, our heroes are about to witness the battle of their lives!
media.title: Flash of the Titans!

media.description: After seeing Leon battle in the World Coronation Series, Ash knows just what he has to do!
media.title: The Climb to Be the Very Best!

media.description: Our heroes’ trip to the Unova region is filled with lots of twists and turns, and an unexpected surprise tops it off!
media.title: Raid Battle in The Ruins!

media.description: Some snowy weather gives Goh the opportunity to reunite with family and make a new friend!
media.title: A Snow Day for Searching!

media.description: What begins as a curse for our hero ends up being a wonderful surprise for all!
media.title: A Chilling Curse!

media.description: Goh and Scorbunny have different ideas about training—with unexpected results!
media.title: Kicking It from Here Into Tomorrow!

media.description: Ash is just starting out on the road to a rematch with Leon, but the action is already electrifying!
media.title: Destination: Coronation!

media.description: A Ditto with a case of stage fright gets some help from the most unlikely of sources!
media.title: A Talent for Imitation!

media.description: Professor Cerise has a big event planned, and our heroes are the key to its success!
media.title: Dreams Are Made of These!

media.description: Intrigued by an unusual Pokémon Egg, Ash agrees to care for it—leading to even more excitement!
media.title: Caring for a Mystery!

media.description: Our heroes are doing research in Littleroot Town, and as usual, the results are anything but usual!
media.title: Goodbye, Friend!

media.description: Although Cerise Park is beautiful to behold, sometimes there’s trouble in paradise!
media.title: Panic in the Park!

media.description: A day of rest and relaxation is anything but relaxing for Team Rocket!
media.title: A Little Rocket R & R!

media.description: As he rises in the World Coronation Series rankings, Ash finds himself facing an old friend and formidable opponent!
media.title: A Festival Reunion!

media.description: Some unusual events place our heroes among the wildest assortment of Trainers and Pokémon imaginable!
media.title: Splash, Dash, and Smash for the Crown! / Slowking's Crowning!

media.description: A visit to a major battle event not only leads our heroes to new adventures, but to new friends as well!
media.title: Toughing It Out!

media.description: A chance encounter with a timid Pokémon brings out emotions in everybody!
media.title: Sobbing Sobble!

media.description: Chloe and her family come together to help an injured Pokémon, but its recovery has unexpected side effects!
media.title: There's a New Kid in Town!

media.description: Ash gets caught up in some intensive special training, but not everyone is happy about it!
media.title: Betrayed, Bothered, and Beleaguered!

media.description: The bond between people and Pokémon can translate into spectacular magic!
media.title: The Cuteness Quotient!

media.description: A family vacation takes Goh on a trip down memory lane!
media.title: Time After Time!

media.description: An encounter with an ardent Bug-type Trainer gives our heroes a chance for some up-close-and-personal Bug-type adventures!
media.title: Trade, Borrow, and Steal!

media.description: A World Coronation Series battle against Gym Leader Bea challenges Ash like never before!
media.title: Solitary and Menacing!

media.description: Goh’s goal of catching one of every kind of Pokémon leads our heroes to an electrifying encounter!
media.title: Gotta Catch a What?!

media.description: Our heroes are determined to find out what’s inside a raging sandstorm—with lots of twists and turns along the way!
media.title: Making Battles in the Sand!

media.description: Our heroes are off to Alola, and the Pokémon School gang has some surprises in store for them!
media.title: That New Old Gang of Mine!

media.description: A visit to the Pewter Museum of Science sets our heroes on an ancient and thrilling adventure!
media.title: Restore and Renew!

media.description: Our heroes head to the Johto region so Ash can have a rematch with Bea!
media.title: Octo-Gridlock at the Gym!

media.description: Our heroes are hot on the trail of a Legendary Pokémon and the answer to a mystery!
media.title: A Crackling Raid Battle!

media.description: It’s an unusual day for everyone: heroes and foes alike!
media.title: Pikachu Translation Check… Up to Your Neck!

media.description: Dynamax Pokémon are rampaging in Galar, and our heroes are hot on the trail of discovery!
media.title: Sword and Shield, Slumbering Weald!

media.description: Approaching the crisis in Galar from different perspectives, our heroes are determined to find answers!
media.title: Sword and Shield: The Darkest Day!

media.description: As the Galar region faces possible destruction, our heroes are determined to prevent that from happening!
media.title: Sword and Shield: From Here to Eternatus!

media.description: Our heroes face a challenge of unfathomable proportions, and the fate of Galar hangs in the balance!
media.title: Sword and Shield…The Legends Awaken!

media.description: As Ash and Goh explore a distant island in search of Mew, their research takes an unexpected, powerful turn!
media.title: Getting More Than You Battled For!

media.description: There’s a big competition in Vermilion City, and heroes and villains alike are digging in to win!
media.title: Crowning the Chow Crusher!

media.description: As Ash and Goh enjoy their eatery tour in Unova, two of their Pokémon bond in ways they never dreamed!
media.title: A Close Call… Practically!

channel_description: The journey continues on Pokémon TV! Watch episodes from the new Pokémon the Series: Sun & Moon—Ultra Legends season today!
channel_name: Pokémon the Series: Sun & Moon—Ultra Legends

media.description: The Pokémon School class is putting on a play with more twists and turns than they could ever expect!
media.title: Lillier and the Staff!

media.description: Harper and Sarah are excited to visit a haunted house, and they end up having a bit too much fun!
media.title: A Haunted House for Everyone!

media.description: Some unusual activity is occurring around Wela Volcano, but the Ultra Guardians are on the case!
media.title: Sparking Confusion!

media.description: While Ash runs an errand to Aether Paradise, a certain trio of troublemakers sets out to catch Pokémon there!
media.title: Don’t Ignore the Small Stufful!

media.description: A chance meeting with another Trainer gives Ash and Rowlet new battle experiences they never imagined!
media.title: No Stone Unturned!

media.description: Rotom Dex’s love of the hit TV show Alolan Detective Laki produces some unexpected results!
media.title: Bright Lights, Big Changes!

media.description: An ocean-loving Eevee has traveled many miles…and where one journey ends, another is about to begin!
media.title: We Know Where You’re Going, Eevee!

media.description: A spur-of-the-moment battle with Tapu Koko results in an unexpected, unbelievable journey for Ash and Pikachu!
media.title: Battling the Beast Within!

media.description: Our heroes are grappling with an Alola region in a parallel world—and they’ve appeared just in time to help save it!
media.title: Parallel Friendships!

media.description: At the start of their break, the Pokémon School students have visitors—and Ash can’t believe his eyes!
media.title: Alola, Alola!

media.description: Misty and Brock continue to enjoy their Alola region vacation, but there are some who would like that to stop!
media.title: Heart of Fire, Heart of Stone!

media.description: Our heroes are visiting Poni Island for their school research projects, but they’re not the only ones with big plans!
media.title: That’s Some Spicy Island Research!

media.description: Ash’s research project is all about battling, but who will that battling involve?
media.title: Showdown on Poni Island!

media.description: As the Pokémon School class continues their research projects on Poni Island, Sophocles and Lana have some big surprises in store!
media.title: Evolving Research!

media.description: Our heroes’ research projects continue on Poni Island, and now is the time for Kiawe and Mallow to shine!
media.title: Run, Heroes, Run!

media.description: A visit to Hapu’s farm envelops our heroes in an experience they will never forget!
media.title: Memories in the Mist!

media.description: The Pokémon School students have one more research project to complete, and it’s sure to generate excitement and electricity for everyone!
media.title: A Grand Debut!

media.description: When the Pokémon School class meets an accomplished Pokémon Golfer, they learn some valuable lessons and have fun at the same time!
media.title: Keeping Your Eyes on the Ball!

media.description: Our heroes have made an incredible discovery, and they’re just beginning to digest the details!
media.title: Show Me the Metal!

media.description: Our heroes have discovered a new species of Pokémon named Meltan, and one Meltan in particular has discovered a new friend!
media.title: Got Meltan?

media.description: An appearance on a TV quiz show leads our heroes into a world they only dreamed of!
media.title: This Magik Moment!

media.description: Alola is facing another crisis, and the Ultra Guardians are facing a double shift!
media.title: Beauty Is Only Crystal Deep!

media.description: Professor Kukui’s big announcement is making unexpected waves with unexpected people!
media.title: The Dealer of Destruction!

media.description: An emotional look into the past reveals astounding people and places, and nothing will ever be the same again!
media.title: The Secret Princess!

media.description: Our heroes’ visit to a popular tourist attraction ends up being anything but a breeze!
media.title: Drawn with the Wind!

media.description: A second day in Malie City provides our heroes with a hard-earned chance for some unexpected excitement!
media.title: Aiming for the Top Floor!

media.description: Sophocles may be excited to compete in a favorite race, but winning is about much more than coming in first!
media.title: A High-Speed Awakening!

media.description: What starts as an ordinary fishing expedition turns into a much bigger adventure than anyone could have imagined!
media.title: The One That Didn’t Get Away!

media.description: When Mallow sets out on a routine errand, little does she know she’ll return with much more than she ever dreamed of!
media.title: A Recipe for Success!

media.description: One of Team Rocket’s questionable claims comes back to haunt them when they’re paid a visit by Giovanni’s assistant Matori!
media.title: Spying for the Big Guy!

media.description: Our heroes can’t wait to start training for the upcoming Alola Pokémon League, but not everyone is feeling confident!
media.title: A Fiery Training Camp Trick!

media.description: Objects are being cut into pieces all over Melemele Island, and the Ultra Guardians set out to investigate!
media.title: Living on the Cutting Edge!

media.description: An unexpected encounter with an unexpected Pokémon takes Ash on an adventure he’ll never forget!
media.title: A Timeless Encounter!

media.description: While Ash was caught up in an untimely adventure, his Pokémon were having quite an adventure of their own!
media.title: Pikachu’s Exciting Adventure!

media.description: The Alola Pokémon League is off to a rousing start, and emotions are running high in and out of Manalo Stadium!
media.title: Chasing Memories, Creating Dreams!

media.description: The Alola Pokémon League is gearing up for a thrilling opening, but there seems to be trouble ahead…
media.title: League Offenders and Defenders!

media.description: The Alola Pokémon League is off to a rousing start with a Battle Royal competition among friends and rivals both old and new!
media.title: Battle Royal 151!

media.description: As the Alola Pokémon League marches on, friends and rivals alike give it their all!
media.title: Battling Besties!

media.description: The Alola Pokémon League is in full swing, and there’s no shortage of surprises in store!
media.title: The Battlefield of Truth and Love!

media.description: As Ash and Rowlet prepare for their battle against Hau in the Alola Pokémon League, they get a little help from some old friends!
media.title: Imitation Is the Sincerest Form of Strategy!

media.description: As the Alola Pokémon League quarterfinals continue, Ash and Rowlet’s battle against Hau and Decidueye takes plenty of twists and turns!
media.title: Battling on the Wing!

media.description: The Alola Pokémon League quarterfinals are wrapping up, and today’s event promises to be a wild ride!
media.title: The Road to the Semifinals!

media.description: The first match of the Alola Pokémon League semifinals is up next, and the final four Trainers are determined to come out on top!
media.title: The Final Four!

media.description: As the Alola Pokémon League nears the finals, the stakes are getting higher, and temperatures are rising to a fever pitch!
media.title: Getting Down to the Ire!

media.description: The second round of the Alola Pokémon League semifinals is proceeding at a rapid pace, and there’s a lot more going on than meets the eye!
media.title: The Wisdom Not to Run!

media.description: It’s time for the Alola Pokémon League finals, and the competitors are more determined than ever to become Champion!
media.title: Final Rivals!

media.description: The Alola Pokémon League is down to the final moments of the final battle! Who will emerge victorious?
media.title: Enter the Champion!

media.description: Although the Alola Pokémon League is over, a new type of excitement is just beginning!
media.title: Z-Move Showdown!

media.description: The Alola Pokémon League’s exhibition match is off to a fiery start—just as expected for a battle between Ash and the now-unmasked Masked Royal!
media.title: Exhibition Unmasked!

media.description: In the air or on the ground, the Alola Pokémon League’s exhibition match between Ash and Professor Kukui is roaring along!
media.title: A Full Battle Bounty!

media.description: The exhibition match between Ash and Professor Kukui continues with a long-awaited fiery showdown!
media.title: Fiery Surprises!

media.description: Ash’s win at the Alola Pokémon League was astounding—but the resulting exhibition match has some colossal surprises in store, too!
media.title: From Z to Shining Z!

media.description: Now that the Alola Pokémon League is over, it’s time for the Pokémon School class to make plans for their upcoming vacation!
media.title: Dreaming of the Sun and Moon!

media.description: With their big vacation on the horizon, our heroes are setting some life-changing plans into motion!
media.title: Thank You, Alola! The Journey Continues!

channel_name: Pokémon the Series: Sun & Moon—Ultra Adventures

media.description: A vivid dream has set our hero on a mission to find out its true meaning!
media.title: A Dream Encounter!

media.description: As our heroes get to know Nebby better, Nebby gets to know them better, too!
media.title: Now You See Them, Now You Don’t!

media.description: While our heroes explore one part of Aether Paradise, Team Rocket is busy exploring another!
media.title: Deceiving Appearances!

media.description: Ash and his friends are off on another big adventure, thanks to Nebby’s amazing powers!
media.title: A Masked Warning!

media.description: A sleepover at Professor Kukui’s house sets the stage for fun, friendship, and unexpected adventure!
media.title: Night of a Thousand Poses!

media.description: Lillie is on a mission to put her past behind her once and for all!
media.title: Mission: Total Recall!

media.description: Although Faba’s original sinister plot has been foiled, he isn’t about to give up on his dream!
media.title: Faba’s Revenge!

media.description: Lusamine has been captured by an Ultra Beast and swept away through an Ultra Wormhole, but everyone is determined to get her back safely!
media.title: Family Determination!

media.description: Our heroes are determined to rescue Lusamine, and help is coming from unexpected and astounding sources!
media.title: Revealing the Stuff of Legend!

media.description: Our heroes are determined to rescue Lusamine from inside the Ultra Wormhole, but Lusamine has other ideas!
media.title: Rescuing the Unwilling!

media.description: Our heroes are doing everything they can to save Lusamine from an Ultra Beast…while Lusamine is doing everything she can to stop them!
media.title: 10,000,000 Reasons to Fight!

media.description: Professors Kukui and Burnet are getting married, and our heroes know just what to do to help!
media.title: The Professors’ New Adventure!

media.description: Our heroes are wondering about Komala’s sleep patterns when they’re interrupted by a familiar visitor!
media.title: Let Sleeping Pokémon Lie!

media.description: Rotom Dex embarks on an electrifying journey—whether it wants to or not!
media.title: The Dex Can’t Help It!

media.description: An accidental encounter with the past puts the present and future in jeopardy!
media.title: Fighting Back the Tears!

media.description: A distant memory shared by Mallow and Lana is rekindled in a bittersweet way!
media.title: Tasting the Bitter with the Sweet!

media.description: A trip to Mount Lanakila gives our heroes the opportunity to learn and grow in ways they hadn’t imagined!
media.title: Getting a Jump on the Competition!

media.description: The appearance of another Ultra Beast compels our heroes to take on new roles—and take charge!
media.title: A Mission of Ultra Urgency!

media.description: An unexpected appearance by a cunning visitor is turning Team Rocket’s world on its head!
media.title: Acting True to Form!

media.description: The appearance of a popular Alolan battling duo brings out some surprising fiery determination!
media.title: Pushing the Fiery Envelope!

media.description: A visit by a surprise Pokémon School graduate dazzles our heroes with the stuff of legends!
media.title: Turning Heads and Training Hard!

media.description: Pokémon School graduate Ilima teaches our heroes about an activity that’s near and dear to his heart!
media.title: Smashing with Sketch!

media.description: Our heroes are about to welcome an unexpected addition into the family—unexpected in so many delightful ways!
media.title: Love at First Twirl!

media.description: Nurse Joy is feeling a bit under the weather today, but we know just the heroes to help her out!
media.title: Real Life…Inquire Within!

media.description: A potential disaster threatens the future of the Alola region, but the Ultra Guardians are ready, willing, and able to deal with it!
media.title: Rise and Shine, Starship!

media.description: The survival of Kiawe’s family farm may be at stake, but our heroes are up to the challenge!
media.title: The Young Flame Strikes Back!

media.description: There are lots of interesting Pokémon for our heroes to discover in Alola, and the one they meet today is no exception!
media.title: Dewpider Ascending!

media.description: There’s a big baking competition coming up in Alola, and a surprising participant is joining in on the fun!
media.title: Sours for the Sweet!

media.description: Team Rocket appears to be stuck in a rut, but solutions can come from high places!
media.title: Why Not Give Me a Z-Ring Sometime?

media.description: A series of smaller trials line the pathway to Ash’s goal—a grand trial!
media.title: Tough Guy Trials!

media.description: Ash is determined to train with Tapu Bulu, and Tapu Bulu is determined to be as unpredictable as ever!
media.title: Some Kind of Laziness!

media.description: Ash and Pikachu are all set for their rematch against the island kahuna, but Nanu has a different idea!
media.title: A Battle Hand-Off!

media.description: Ash challenges Kahuna Nanu in the Ula’ula Island grand trial. In order to win, Ash must defeat three of Nanu’s Pokémon with only one of his. Can Lycanroc pull through?
media.title: Guiding an Awakening!

media.description: The Ultra Guardians are being called upon again, but this time, they’re on double duty!
media.title: Twirling with a Bang!

media.description: Our heroes are stargazing, little suspecting the spectacle that awaits them in the night sky!
media.title: Showering the World with Love!

media.description: A surprising show of determination leads to a happy outcome for many—in many different ways!
media.title: Not Caving Under Pressure!

media.description: The Battle Royal Dome is ablaze with battling excitement, but this time the Masked Royal has a little help!
media.title: A Young Royal Flame Ignites!

media.description: A rousing Pokémon School class project has everyone out of their chairs, and out on the floor!
media.title: All They Want to Do Is Dance, Dance!

media.description: When Faba appoints himself professor for the day at the Pokémon School, an unexpected event shows that big adventures can come in small packages!
media.title: Dummy, You Shrunk the Kids!

media.description: Our heroes have met an astoundingly talented artist, but there’s much more to her and her partner than meets the eye!
media.title: The Shape of Love to Come!

media.description: Another Ultra Beast has made its way to Alola, and the Ultra Guardians have an ultra-gigantic mission on their hands!
media.title: The Long Vault Home!

media.description: Everybody’s looking forward to a relaxing day at a health spa, although a few secretly have different plans!
media.title: I Choose Paradise!

media.description: Things are not right in Alola, and our heroes are poised to find out why!
media.title: Filling the Light with Darkness!

media.description: A mysterious creature has emerged from an Ultra Wormhole and now appears to be threatening Alola, but our heroes are ready to do anything they can to help!
media.title: Full Moon and Many Arms!

media.description: Our heroes are on a mission to rescue Solgaleo from UB Black’s clutches, and what a mission it is turning out to be!
media.title: The Prism Between Light and Darkness!

media.description: The Ultra Guardians are on a mission to save Poipole’s world, and everyone and everything depends on them!
media.title: Securing the Future!

media.description: The rumors are true, and our heroes can’t pika-believe what they find!
media.title: A Plethora of Pikachu!

media.description: It’s time for the Masked Royal to face his old rival in the ring, but first, there are a few obstacles to be dealt with!
media.title: Turning the Other Mask!

media.description: What begins as a vacation for our hero on Melemele Island in the Alola region turns into the promise of many, many exciting adventures to come!
media.title: Alola to New Adventure!

media.description: Ash and Pikachu are adjusting to life in the Alola region—and it’s about to give them a powerful push in a new direction!
media.title: The Guardian’s Challenge!

media.description: Ash’s journey in the Alola region is just getting under way, and our hero has a new partner to share it with!
media.title: Loading the Dex!

media.description: Ash is after his first Pokémon in the Alola region, and the adventure that ensues is typical Ash!
media.title: First Catch in Alola, Ketchum-Style!

media.description: Ash’s Pokémon class is off to the sea for some fishing, but Team Rocket has a completely different kind of fishing in mind!
media.title: Yo, Ho, Ho! Go, Popplio!

media.description: Ash’s first day off from Pokémon School was supposed to be a relaxing break, but things don’t go quite as expected!
media.title: A Shocking Grocery Run!

media.description: A feisty Litten is determined to steal food from others, and Ash and Pikachu are determined to find out why!
media.title: That's Why the Litten Is a Scamp!

media.description: Lillie has a Pokémon Egg to care for until it hatches, but will fear get in her way?
media.title: Lillie's Egg-Xhilarating Challenge!

media.description: Ash is determined to undergo the island challenge and replace his Z-Crystal, so Professor Kukui takes him to meet Hala, the kahuna of Melemele Island.
media.title: To Top a Totem!

media.description: The Melemele Island grand trial is imminent, and Ash must square off against the power and wisdom of Kahuna Hala!
media.title: Trial and Tribulation!

media.description: Ash has time off from school for training, but a fellow student’s activities away from school have our hero wanting to find out all about it!
media.title: Young Kiawe Had a Farm!

media.description: While our heroes enjoy a class on the beach, familiar and unfamiliar troubles are brewing behind the scenes!
media.title: The Sun, the Scare, the Secret Lair!

media.description: An Alolan tradition whets everyone’s appetite for fun, and Ash decides to join in!
media.title: Racing to a Big Event!

media.description: The time has come for Lillie to address her fears, and having a new friend is the perfect way to do it!
media.title: Getting to Know You!

media.description: Rockruff’s current behavior may be a mystery, but Ash and Professor Kukui are determined to get to the bottom of it!
media.title: Rocking Clawmark Hill!

media.description: Team Rocket has their eyes on our heroes’ Pokémon, but a mysterious third Pokémon has a different idea!
media.title: They Might Not Be Giants!

media.description: There’s a mystery that needs solving, and there’s also a surprising sleuth who’s determined to solve it!
media.title: Crystal-Clear Sleuthing!

media.description: Rotom Dex is eager to help solve the mystery of Ash’s missing Z-Crystal!
media.title: A Seasoned Search!

media.description: Ash is looking for a very important rematch, and his training regimen is breaking new ground!
media.title: A Guardian Rematch!

media.description: A pleasant day trip for our heroes turns into an unforgettable adventure!
media.title: Partner Promises!

media.description: The ending of one chapter in the life of a determined Pokémon ushers in the beginning of a brand-new one!
media.title: One Journey Ends, Another Begins...

media.description: A day at the beach offers up our heroes much more than they bargained for!
media.title: A Shivering Shovel Search!

media.description: A major force in Alolan popular music is on the verge of collapse!
media.title: Getting the Band Back Together!

media.description: It’s Open House day at the Pokémon School, and a surprising group of people has gathered for all the fun!
media.title: Alolan Open House!

media.description: There’s a Z-Crystal ripe for the picking, but are the unlikely pickers up to the task?
media.title: A Team-on-Team Tussle!

media.description: Moving to a new place and a new life can be stressful for anyone, and the Pokémon School gang is no exception!
media.title: So Long, Sophocles!

media.description: A powerful Trainer has recently appeared on Melemele Island, and Ash can’t wait to find out everything about him!
media.title: A Glaring Rivalry!

media.description: It’s Pokémon Base season in Alola, and the Pokémon School gang can’t seem to get enough of it: even playing against the enemy!
media.title: Pulling Out the Pokémon Base Pepper!

media.description: A Pokémon School camping trip, complete with a scary campfire story, makes for an experience our heroes will never forget!
media.title: Lulled to La-La Land!

media.description: An unusual assignment at the Pokémon School gives our heroes a surprising opportunity to learn, grow, and have fun at the same time!
media.title: The Ol’ Raise and Switch!

media.description: Our heroes are preparing for a field trip on Akala Island, and the island kahuna promises to make it a trip to remember!
media.title: The Island Whisperer!

media.description: It’s a new day for the Pokémon School field trip, and our heroes are preparing for an adventure they will treasure forever!
media.title: Treasure Hunt, Akala Style!

media.description: Our heroes are busy with extracurricular activities on Akala Island, and Ash and Lana are in for a great adventure!
media.title: Big Sky, Small Fry!

media.description: The Wela Fire Festival is just starting to heat up, but someone seems determined to extinguish the celebration!
media.title: A Crowning Moment of Truth!

media.description: Our heroes are embarking on a mission filled with good taste…and a surprising finish!
media.title: Currying Favor and Flavor!

media.description: The time for Ash’s grand trial with Olivia is finally here, and it’s no ordinary battle!
media.title: Trials and Determinations!

media.description: As if Ash’s victory at his grand trial wasn’t monumental enough, an unexpected transformation makes a memorable field trip even more momentous!
media.title: Rising from the Ruins!

media.description: When Mimikyu faces a fashion problem, Jessie sees a bonding opportunity!
media.title: Mimikyu Unmasked!

media.description: It’s a challenging day for Mallow and her family restaurant, and emotions are running high!
media.title: Mallow and the Forest Teacher!

media.description: Lana and Popplio are working hard to master their Z-Move, but their progress is soon to grow by leaps and bounds!
media.title: Balloons, Brionne, and Belligerence!

media.description: Three of our heroes are teaming up for the annual Charjabug race, an electrifying event with shocking results!
media.title: Mounting an Electrifying Charge!

media.description: A celebratory Pokémon School class trip turns out to be a reunion no one will ever forget!
media.title: Alola, Kanto!

media.description: The Cerulean Gym is the setting for old and new friends, battling old and new skills!
media.title: When Regions Collide!

channel_description: Ash, Pikachu, and their friends continue their adventure in the Sinnoh region as Pokémon: DP Battle Dimension arrives on Pokémon TV!

media.description: As our heroes head towards Veilstone City, Ash's new Chimchar struggles to adapt to its new surroundings.
media.title: Tears for Fears

media.description: Ash and his friends run into Gardenia, the Eterna Gym Leader, in the middle of her travels through Sinnoh.
media.title: Once There Were Greenfields

media.description: Ash has Chimchar and Aipom battle each other to train for his upcoming Gym battle. But Buizel is distracted by the battle between Chimchar and Aipom.
media.title: Throwing the Track Switch

media.description: Aipom and Buizel are battling in a field when Aipom deflects Buizel's Sonic Boom into an old stone tower, knocking it down.
media.title: The Keystone Pops

media.description: On the way to Solaceon Town, our heroes reach a river with an unfinished bridge. Brock immediately falls for Isis, the stonecutter working on the bridge.
media.title: Bibarel Gnaws Best

media.description: On Mt. Coronet, Ash and Turtwig are battling Alan, an energetic Trainer with a Nosepass. The only place Nosepass can evolve into Probopass is Mt. Coronet, so Alan is eager to have all the battles he can.
media.title: Nosing 'Round the Mountain

media.description: Hoping to find a place to stay for the night, our heroes visit an imposing manor. Instead, they're almost mistaken for thieves by Marble, a self-proclaimed Super-Duper Ace Detective.
media.title: Luxray Vision

media.description: Deep in training for the Solaceon Contest, Dawn shows off Aipom's latest Contest move and discovers that Aipom has actually learned a new move: Double Hit!
media.title: Journey to the Unown

media.description: The Solaceon Contest is about to start, and Dawn is eager to show off her Ambipom's spectacular Swift move.
media.title: Team Shocker

media.description: Brock leads his friends to the Mountain Hut Maid Café, where waitresses Spring, Summer, and Autumn serve up fresh Miltank milk.
media.title: Tanks for the Memories

media.description: When it's late and there's no Pokémon Center nearby, Dawn comes up with the solution: a visit to a nearby hot spring hotel, owned by the parents of her old friend Leona!
media.title: Hot Springing a Leak

media.description: As Ash and his friends pass through a city, a Gliscor and a group of Gligar swarm them and gobble up all their lunch. What's more, Paul is also in town with his Murkrow—it looks like he's after Gliscor!
media.title: Riding the Winds of Change

media.description: There's still a desert to cross before Ash can reach Veilstone City and the next Gym, but our heroes decide to let their Pokémon out to play in the sand.
media.title: Sleight of Sand

media.description: Just as they reach Veilstone City, Ash and his friends spot a nearby commotion and track it down to the source: Gym Leader Maylene and her Lucario, locked in an intense sparring session!
media.title: Lost Leader Strategy

media.description: Dawn has challenged Maylene, the Veilstone Gym Leader, to a battle that's scheduled for the next day. This gives both Dawn and Ash time to train.
media.title: Crossing the Battle Line

media.description: Dawn's Veilstone Gym challenge has restored Gym Leader Maylene's confidence, so Maylene is now ready to accept Ash's own Gym challenge.
media.title: A Triple Fighting Chance

media.description: Before Ash and his friends leave Veilstone City, Paul's brother Reggie shows him the city's most famous sight: a field full of ancient meteorites that are considered the guardians of the city.
media.title: Enter Galactic

media.description: It's another day on the road for our heroes: Ash and Gligar practice, while Dawn and Buneary study the latest Poké Chic fashion trends.
media.title: The Bells Are Singing

media.description: Dazzled by dreams of success, Jessie and Dustox train on the shores of a beautiful mountain lake. Jessie's Dustox is then distracted by an unfamiliar Dustox.
media.title: Crossing Paths

media.description: Before he can get to Pastoria City, Ash has to battle a slang-talking Trainer named Sho. Sho wants to collect a Pikachu evolution set and he already has Raichu and Pichu, so he has his eye on Ash's Pikachu.
media.title: Pika and Goliath

media.description: Wallace, a Coordinator star and former Gym Leader, is bringing his Wallace Cup event to the shores of Sinnohs Lake Valor.
media.title: Our Cup Runneth Over

media.description: May has arrived at Lake Valor to see her old friends and compete in the Wallace Cup. She's brought presents for everyone and a new Pokémon, Glaceon—it's the new Evolution of her trusty Eevee.
media.title: A Full Course Tag Battle

media.description: The day before the Wallace Cup, Zoey shows up at Lake Valor for the competition.
media.title: Staging a Heroes' Welcome

media.description: With Dawn and her friends safely past the appeals round of the Wallace Cup, the girls enjoy an opportunity to sit back and chat while Ash, who can't sleep, decides to take a walk near Lake Valor.
media.title: Pruning a Passel of Pals

media.description: It's the semifinal round of the Wallace Cup and Dawn's Piplup is battling hard against Kyle's Crawdaunt.
media.title: Strategy With a Smile

media.description: On the way to Pastoria City, Ash and his friends meet Tyler and his Piplup, Pippy. The pair is hot on the trail of a Yanma.
media.title: The Thief That Keeps On Thieving

media.description: While Ash's Pokémon train for the upcoming Pastoria Gym battle, Gligar is blown away by a sudden gust of wind. Gligar lands on Team Rocket's balloon—accidentally ripping a hole in it with its claws.
media.title: Chim-Charred

media.description: Ash has reached the Pastoria City Gym, but there's no Gym battling today—the Gym Leader, Crasher Wake, is off to the Pastoria Great Marsh.
media.title: Cream of the Croagunk Crop!

media.description: In the middle of the night, chaos breaks loose in an isolated research center as research subject RX-1, a Riolu, escapes with the help of several men and a getaway truck.
media.title: Pokémon Ranger and the Kidnapped Riolu! Part 1

media.description: Pokémon Hunter J has trapped Ash and a kidnapped Riolu in the heart of a blazing forest fire so she can capture Riolu for her client—and Ash is unable to stop her from seizing Riolu and flying away!
media.title: Pokémon Ranger and the Kidnapped Riolu! Part 2

media.description: It's the day after Pastoria City's Croagunk Festival—and while Team Rocket may have time to enjoy a leisurely marsh mud bath, Ash and his Pokémon must train for their Pastoria Gym battle.
media.title: A Crasher Course in Power!

media.description: Ash and his friends are saved from a sudden rainstorm when Monica, a housekeeper, invites them to stay at Mr. Backlot's mansion. Old Mr. Backlot is a wealthy man who's turned the area into a Trophy Garden for his Pokémon.
media.title: Hungry for the Good Life!

media.description: As Ash heads back to Hearthome City for his long-delayed Gym battle, he's concerned about his own Gligar's battle woes. Even though Ash gives Gligar lots of special training, it just can't get its act together.
media.title: Fighting Fear With Fear

media.description: Ash and his friends have returned to Hearthome City for Ash's Gym Battle, but Gym Leader Fantina is still out of town.
media.title: Arriving in Style

media.description: Our heroes are on the path to Celestic Town, but the road runs through a narrow pass that's blocked by three irritable Psyduck. If Ash and his friends take a detour, they'll miss the Celestic Town Contest.
media.title: The Psyduck Stops Here!

media.description: Ash and his friends are just in time for the Pokémon Summer Academy at Professor Rowan's research facility on Mt. Coronet, where young Trainers have gathered to make new friends and learn about Pokémon.
media.title: Camping It Up!

media.description: It's the third day of Professor Rowan's Pokémon Summer Academy, and he's sent the campers to observe Water-type Pokémon living in a nearby lake.
media.title: Up Close and Personable

media.description: On the fifth day of the Pokémon Summer Academy, Professor Rowan has a special assignment for his campers: they'll each team up with a partner and go to the Summit Ruins at night.
media.title: Ghoul Daze

media.description: The Pokémon Summer Academy is almost over, but there's one more event left: the Pokémon Triathlon!
media.title: One Team, Two Team, Red Team, Blue Team!

media.description: Dawn and Piplup are hard at work on a new BubbleBeam combination, but Piplup works so hard that it passes out from exhaustion! Dawn and the gang rush Piplup to a Pokémon Center for some much-needed rest.
media.title: A Lean Mean Team Rocket Machine!

media.description: Dawn and her friends are passing through a town on their way to the Celestic Contest when they see Zoey in the middle of a tough battle with a well-dressed Coordinator.
media.title: Playing the Leveling Field

media.description: On the way to Celestic Town, Ash and his friends are camped at a mountain cabin. While Dawn trains and Ash snoozes, Brock goes down the mountain to visit a pharmacy.
media.title: Doc Brock

media.description: Dawn heads to the Celestic Town Contest, only to find that Lila is among the competition! Lila's making her big comeback, and she puts on a great show with her Cherrim.
media.title: Battling the Generation Gap

media.description: Team Galactic has just stolen the Adamant Orb from a transport plane headed to Celestic Town, and their next target could be the Lustrous Orb stored in the town's research center.
media.title: Losing Its Lustrous!

media.description: Team Galactic Commanders Saturn and Mars have cornered Cynthia, her grandmother Carolina, the business mogul Cyrus, Officer Jenny's team, and our heroes inside the Celestic Town research center.
media.title: A Double Team Turnover

media.description: On the way to Solaceon Town, Ash and his friends hear that the local "Scarf Monster" has made the tabloid news. Ash is skeptical, even though he and his friends see a shadow in the forest that looks much like the rumored monster itself.
media.title: If the Scarf Fits, Wear It

media.description: Ash and his friends enter a small town where all the girls are lined up to watch Aaron, one of the Elite Four, conduct a public training session.
media.title: A Trainer and Child Reunion

media.description: Ash and his friends run into a Pokémon Center to watch a big battle on the TV: Champion Cynthia defeating Elite Four Aaron!
media.title: Aiding the Enemy

media.description: As Ash enters the Hearthome Gym for his Gym Challenge, he collides with a blond Trainer in a hurry! The Trainer races off down the street, leaving his badge case behind.
media.title: Barry's Busting Out All Over

media.description: Ash is ready to battle Hearthome Gym Leader Fantina for the second time, with both his pride and the Relic Badge at stake.
media.title: Shield With a Twist

media.description: Barry joins Ash and the gang as they take a blimp to Canalave City. As soon as they disembark, Team Rocket—disguised as photographers—offers to take a commemorative picture of everyone and their Pokémon.
media.title: Jumping Rocket Ship

media.description: Ash arrives at the Canalave Gym, only to hear bad news: the Gym Leader is away on Iron Island, and the locals are all sleep-deprived due to horrible nightmares!
media.title: Sleepless in Pre-Battle

channel_description: Travel to the Sinnoh region with Ash and Pikachu as Pokémon: Diamond and Pearl arrives on Pokémon TV!

media.description: It's always exciting when new Pokémon Trainers receives their first Pokémon, but for a girl named Dawn, things will be far more exciting than she'd ever imagined!
media.title: Following a Maiden's Voyage

media.description: Dawn and Piplup's Pokémon journey is off to a bumpy start! She needs to catch Pokémon so she can become a great Pokémon Coordinator like her mom, but both her and Piplup are having trouble getting the hang of things.
media.title: Two Degrees of Separation

media.description: Paul catches a Starly and challenges Ash to a battle—but without Pikachu, Ash doesn't have enough Pokémon for a 3-on-3 battle!
media.title: When Pokémon Worlds Collide

media.description: Dawn is still trying to catch her first wild Pokémon, but Ash's coaching isn't helping at all and both Trainers are getting annoyed.
media.title: Dawn of a New Era

media.description: Team Rocket's latest Pikachu-snatching plan slips up, and Pikachu ends up lost in the woods. It's found by a friendly Turtwig who defends Pikachu from Team Rocket, but mistakes Ash for a foe as well!
media.title: Gettin' Twiggy With It

media.description: When Ash runs into his new rival Paul, Ash wants a rematch—and a chance to show off his new Turtwig! The battle takes an unexpected turn when Turtwig disobeys Ash's orders.
media.title: Different Strokes for Different Blokes

media.description: It's a rough day for hero and villain alike, as Dawn's Piplup struggles to perfect a move for the upcoming Pokémon Contest and Team Rocket struggles to find something to eat.
media.title: Like It or Lup It

media.description: There's a new Gym in Sinnoh, and Team Rocket is in charge!
media.title: Gymbaliar

media.description: When Dawn wakes up to a bad hair day, there's only one solution: have Piplup use Bubblebeam to fix her hair!
media.title: Setting the World on its Buneary

media.description: Dawn's first Pokémon Contest is just days away, and in order to prepare, she's searching Jubilife City for a Pokétch—a handy accessory that looks like a watch but has multiple useful functions.
media.title: Not On My Watch Ya Don't

media.description: Dawn's mother Johanna has sent her a special outfit to wear for her first Pokémon Contest, which is just a day away!
media.title: Mounting a Coordinator Assault

media.description: The battles are about to begin in the Jubelife Pokémon Contest, and in the running are Dawn, Ash, Jessie (disguised as Jessilina), and a Coordinator named Zoey.
media.title: Arrival of a Rival

media.description: Ash is traveling through the forest on his way to Oreburgh City, where he hopes to earn his first Gym Badge in Sinnoh.
media.title: A Staravia Is Born

media.description: On the way to Oreburgh, Ash and his friends see Nurse Joy trying to help an injured Nuzleaf. Nuzleaf is too upset to accept her help, so Brock steps in to calm Nuzleaf down.
media.title: Leave It to Brocko!

media.description: Ash and his friends have reached Oreburgh City, where Ash will try to earn his first Sinnoh Gym Badge. But Paul has beaten him to the Oreburgh Gym, and he'll battle Gym Leader Roark first—if Roark ever shows up!
media.title: Shapes of Things to Come

media.description: Ash is in the middle of strategizing for his match when he finds out that Paul gave away his Azumarill because it wasn't tough enough.
media.title: A Gruff Act to Follow

media.description: Dawn tries to convince Ash to send home for Pokémon that are strong against Rock Types, but Ash is persistent on using the ones he currently has.
media.title: Wild in the Streets

media.description: Ash may have lost his battle at the Oreburgh Gym, but he wants a rematch and he's down at the Oreburgh mine to train hard for round two.
media.title: O'er the Rampardos We Watched

media.description: When Dawn comes across a wild Pachirisu, it's so cute that she just has to catch it!
media.title: Twice Smitten, Once Shy

media.description: On the way to Floaroma Town, our heroes see a Salamence-riding woman steal a Gardevoir from a Trainer named Maria. Ash and Pikachu come to the rescue, but the mystery woman sends out a Drapion and swipes Pikachu!
media.title: Mutiny in the Bounty

media.description: As Team Rocket trudges through Sinnoh, they run into the Magikarp Salesman who's tricked them so many times before.
media.title: Ya See We Want an Evolution

media.description: When Ash and his friends pass a village that's holding an informal Pokémon Contest where the prize is a year's supply of fruit, Dawn is eager to enter.
media.title: Borrowing on Bad Faith

media.description: As our Heroes their journey toward Floaroma Town and Dawn’s next Pokemon Contest, they come across a village of Bidoof whose safety is threatened by a rampaging Steelix.
media.title: Faced with Steelix Determination

media.description: Abigail takes Pikachu into the forest, where it uses Thunderbolt to zap berries and give them a delicious roasted flavor. Team Rocket notices this unusual electrical activity and tries to seize Pikachu.
media.title: Cooking Up a Sweet Story

media.description: Dawn and Ash have reached Floaroma Town, the site of Dawn's next Pokémon Contest as well as a Poffin cooking class!
media.title: Oh Do You Know the Poffin Plan

media.description: With time running out before the start of the Floaroma Town Pokémon Contest, Dawn and Pachirisu are getting in as much training as they can.
media.title: Getting the Pre-Contest Titters

media.description: The Floaroma Town Contest has just started, and Dawn's already in trouble! Pachirisu gets spooked before Dawn can even start their appeal, and only Dawn's quick thinking and a Poffin treat can calm it down.
media.title: Settling a Not-So-Old Score

media.description: On the way to Eterna City, our heroes visit a Pokémon Center where they meet young Paige and her big sister Marnie, the daughters of the local Nurse Joy!
media.title: Drifloon on the Wind

media.description: Ash and his friends have come across a newsworthy diversion: two notorious Pokémon Trainers who've won 16 battles in a row, attracting the attention of Rhonda the reporter and her Sinnoh Now news team.
media.title: The Champ Twins

media.description: Ash and his friends find a tree full of delicious honey, the scent of which has attracted several Pokémon, including Ash's Aipom and a wild Burmy. The Burmy has also attracted the attention of a Trainer, Cheryl.
media.title: Some Enchanted Sweetening

media.description: Deep in Eterna Forest, Ash and his friends have joined Cheryl the treasure hunter on her quest to find Enchanted Honey.
media.title: The Grass-type Is Always Greener

media.description: After several adventures, Ash, his friends, and Cheryl the treasure hunter are finally closing in on the elusive Amber Castle.
media.title: An Angry Combeenation

media.description: What could convince our heroes to take a time-out from their journey to Eterna City? A Pokémon Dress-Up Contest where Pokémon try to imitate other Pokémon!
media.title: All Dressed Up With Somewhere to Go

media.description: On the way to Eterna City, our heroes go fishing in hopes of catching a powerful Buizel that's been spotted in a nearby river.
media.title: Buizel Your Way Out of This

media.description: Dawn and Ash are hoping a friendly battle with Turtwig will help Dawn's new Buizel warm up to its new companions. But Buizel wants to play rough, and it won't even listen to Dawn's commands!
media.title: An Elite Meet and Greet

media.description: Ash and his friends are in Eterna City for Ash's next Gym battle, but first they have to help solve a heist at the Eterna Historical Museum!
media.title: A Secret Sphere of Influence

media.description: The time has come for Ash's Eterna Gym Battle with Gym Leader Gardenia, who's a Grass-type Pokémon expert. The battle will be 3-on-3, starting with Ash's Turtwig against Gardenia's Cherubi.
media.title: The Grass Menagerie

media.description: Ash and his friends are taking the Cyling Road toward Hearthome City, but when the weather turns bad and Brock's Pokémon Egg is about to hatch, they quickly take refuge at the nearest Pokémon Center.
media.title: One Big Happiny Family

media.description: On the way to Hearthome City, Ash and his friends spot a sightseeing steamboat and decide to take a ride.
media.title: Steamboat Willies

media.description: When word gets out that Champion League Master Cynthia is in town, our heroes can't resist a chance to meet her in person. But Paul is also in town, and he can't resist challenging Cynthia to a battle!
media.title: Top-Down Training

media.description: Dawn's latest training session is interrupted by a Glameow and Misdreavus that seem to be asking for help, and it's a safe bet that those Pokémon must belong to Zoey!
media.title: A Stand-Up Sit-Down

media.description: On a sunny day in Sinnoh, Ash is literally hit by a bolt out of the blue—an Electrike is practicing its Electric-type moves nearby, but it accidentally zapped Ash instead of its target!
media.title: The Electrike Company

media.description: Brock is surrounded by adoring Nurse Joys and Officer Jennys, Ash is invited to a tournament of the world's greatest Trainers, and Dawn is asked to compete in a Contest of the world's best Coordinators!
media.title: Malice in Wonderland

media.description: Ash's Turtwig brings everyone's attention to a young Hippopotas that's stranded on the ledge of a cliff. Ash hauls the Hippopotas to safety, and it insists on following him.
media.title: Mass Hip-Po-Sis

media.description: Near Mr. Coronet, Ash and his friends come across Pokémon Hunter J's goons trying to snag a group of wild Shieldon. Ash is about to come to their rescue, but his old friend and rival Gary gets there first with his Electivire.
media.title: Ill-Will Hunting

media.description: Dawn needs to turn in her coupon for a new Pokétch application, but she has to do it at the Pokémon Center on the far side of the forest, and time is running out!
media.title: A Maze-ing Race

media.description: On the way to Hearthome City, Ash and his friends are approached by Mira, a friendly girl who offers them a shortcut. All they have to do is use her Abra to teleport there!
media.title: Sandshrew's Locker

media.description: The moment of the Hearthome City Pokemon Contest has finally arrived, and Dawn finds herself competing along with Zoey, Nando, and Jessilina: Jessie in disguise.
media.title: Dawn’s Early Night!

media.description: Dawn is still feeling a little blue after her early exit from the Hearthome Pokémon Contest, so her friends convince her to compete in a tag battle tournament along with Ash and Brock.
media.title: Tag! We're It

media.description: The good news for Ash and his friends is that they've entered a tag battle tournament in Hearthome City and everyone made it past the first round. The bad news? Paul is Ash's partner and the two of them just can't get along.
media.title: Glory Blaze

media.description: After a strange victory in the second round of Hearthome City's tag battle tournament, Paul has abandoned his Chimchar and Ash wants Chimchar to join his team instead.
media.title: Smells Like Team Spirit

channel_description: Ash and Pikachu leave Kanto for the Orange Islands in the second season of Pokémon the Series—see it now on Pokémon TV!
channel_name: Pokémon: Adventures in the Orange Islands

media.description: Misty and Jessie compete against one another for Queen of the Princess Festival, a day where women rule and the guys have to do whatever the girls tell them.
media.title: Princess vs. Princess

media.description: It's Kids Day, and Ash and friends help the children at a nearby school celebrate the holiday.
media.title: The Purr-fect Hero

media.description: Ash, Brock and Misty travel to Cinnabar Island where Ash hopes to win his Volcano Badge.
media.title: Riddle Me This

media.description: Ash continues his quest to attain his Volcano Badge once he finally locates the gym that is suspended above a pool of molten lava!
media.title: Volcanic Panic

media.description: As Ash and the gang are rushing to catch the last ferry off of Cinnabar Island, they stumble over a rare Pokémon in trouble.
media.title: Beach Blank-out Blastoise

media.description: One of Misty's water Pokémon is in desperate need of exercise, so the gang decides to take her Horsea to a gym that's run by her sisters in Cerulean City.
media.title: The Misty Mermaid

media.description: Ash, Brock and Misty get sidetracked on their way to Viridian City when all of their belongings mysteriously disappear.
media.title: Clefairy Tales

media.description: Ash and friends finally make their way to Viridian City where Ash hopes to earn his Earth Badge.
media.title: The Battle of the Badge

media.description: On their way back to Pallet Town, Ash, Brock and Misty encounter a runaway Mr. Mime.
media.title: It's Mr. Mime Time

media.description: Pikachu is lost in a snowy mountain forest! Can Ash and the gang stay warm while tracking down their missing pal?
media.title: Snow Way Out!

media.description: On a visit to Professor Oak's house, Ash runs into Gary where they talk about the upcoming Pokémon League.
media.title: Showdown at the Po-ké Corral

media.description: Ash decides to join his mom and friends who are vacationing on Seafoam Island.
media.title: The Evolution Solution

media.description: In an effort to train hard and maintain top shape for the Pokémon League, Ash decides to try some surfing.
media.title: The Pi-Kahuna

media.description: Back in Pallet Town, Ash and friends meet Florinda who works at the local nursery.
media.title: Make Room for Gloom!

media.description: A famous movie director comes to town and everybody wants to be the star.
media.title: Lights, Camera, Quack-tion!

media.description: The gang heads to Hollywood for the premiere of Pokémon in Love and Meowth is forced to look back on his painful past.
media.title: Go West Young Meowth

media.description: With only three weeks left before the Pokémon League competition, Ash, Brock and Misty head up to Mt. Hideaway to find one of the Elite Four Trainers.
media.title: To Master the Onixpected

media.description: While Ash and Brock are busy training for the Pokémon League, they inadvertently uncover a hidden temple containing Pokémon fossils.
media.title: The Ancient Puzzle of Pokémopolis

media.description: Our heroes are headed to the Pokémon League tournament at the Indigo Plateau when they meet another Trainer going their way. Unfortunately, all of his Gym badges have been stolen, so he can't compete...unless he takes Ash's badges instead!
media.title: Bad to the Bone

media.description: On the day before the Pokémon League Tournament, Ash, Brock and Misty watch as the torchbearer runs by on his way to Indigo stadium.
media.title: All Fired Up!

media.description: It's the first day of the Pokémon League, and when Ash's friends learn his first battle will be held on the Water Field, they're full of advice!
media.title: Round One—Begin!

media.description: Ash's second battle takes place on the Rock Field where he relies on his Squirtle to hopefully take down a Nidorino.
media.title: Fire and Ice

media.description: Ash's fourth battle on the Grass Field is against his toughest opponent yet!
media.title: The Fourth Round Rumble

media.description: Ash's Mom and Professor Oak make a surprise visit to watch Ash battle in the Pokémon League Tournament.
media.title: A Friend in Deed

media.description: A twist of fate pits Ash and his new friend, Richie, against each other in the fifth round of the Pokémon League Competition.
media.title: Friend and Foe Alike

media.description: It's the sixth round match at the Pokémon League Competition, and Ash, Misty and Brock are in the stands cheering for their new friend, Richie.
media.title: Friends to the End

media.description: After battling in the Pokémon League Tournament, Ash and his friends return to Pallet Town for a hero's welcome.
media.title: Pallet Party Panic

media.description: Ash, Brock and Misty prepare for their long journey to Valencia Island to bring back a mysterious Pokéball for Professor Oak.
media.title: A Scare in the Air

media.description: After making a crash landing onto Valencia Island, our heroes get directions to Professor Ivy's laboratory where a mysterious Pokéball is being held.
media.title: Pokéball Peril

media.description: After picking up the GS Ball from Professor Ivy, Brock decided to stay on the island so Ash and Misty head back home by blimp.
media.title: The Lost Lapras

media.description: Ash, Misty and their new friend, Tracey, are on a new adventure exploring the Orange Islands as Ash sets out to qualify for the Orange League Tournament.
media.title: Fit to Be Tide!

media.description: Just as Ash, Misty, and Tracey set foot on Mandarin Island, Pikachu and Togepi turn against them and join a group of other angry Pokémon.
media.title: Pikachu Re-Volts

media.description: While riding around the Orange Islands on his Lapras, Ash finds a mysterious message in a bottle, which leads the gang on a new adventure.
media.title: The Crystal Onix

media.description: Ash and friends are caught in a whirlpool and swept to an unexplored island where all the Pokémon are pink.
media.title: In the Pink

media.description: Aboard Lapras, the group follows a news crew to an uninhabited island, where a scientific expedition is underway after the discovery of a fossilized Kabuto.
media.title: Shell Shock!

media.description: Misty meets another female trainer who also is an expert on water Pokémon. The new trainer notices some signs that Misty's Psyduck may be ready to evolve.
media.title: Bye Bye Psyduck

media.description: While sailing between small islands, the group encounters an extremely busy Nurse Joy.
media.title: The Joy of Pokémon

media.description: A second Orange Islands trainer puts Ash and his Pokémon through a battery of tests.
media.title: Navel Maneuvers

media.description: While Ash and friends are still discovering new islands, they come upon the seven Grapefruit Islands where groves of giant grapefruit are ripe and in season.
media.title: Snack Attack

media.description: Ash, Tracey and Misty find more excitement than they bargain for when they reach their next destination.
media.title: A Shipful of Shivers

media.description: Team Rocket has engine trouble and lands on an island where the natives are waiting for the Great Meowth of Bounty to arrive and fulfill an ancient prophesy.
media.title: Meowth Rules!

media.description: Ash and Tracey are thrilled when they reach Murcott Island, an island famous for having tons of bug-type Pokémon.
media.title: Tracey Gets Bugged

media.description: Team Rocket doesn't take a day off from trying to steal Pikachu... will they catch our heroes off guard?
media.title: A Way Off Day Off

media.description: Our heroes are on their way to Trovita Island when they come across two Pokémon trainers who seemingly hate each other, even though their two Pokémon are in love.
media.title: Wherefore Art Thou, Pokémon?

media.description: Ash, Misty and Tracey are bound for the next Orange League gym on Trovita when they find themselves trekking across rugged landscape, miles from anywhere.
media.title: Git Along, Little Pokémon

media.description: In Trovitopolis City, Ash and friends hear stories about some kind of monster that's been scaring everyone—and when the ground cracks open and dumps them in the sewer, it seems they might meet this monster face to face!
media.title: The Mystery Menace

media.description: After Misty dives into a whirlpool to rescue a girl, she learns that the girl's brother, Rudy, has a giant crush on her. Things get more complicated when it turns out he's also the Gym Leader Ash must challenge next!
media.title: Misty Meets Her Match

media.description: After leaving Trovita Island, Ash and his friends stop off at a place that has a reputation for super-sized Pokémon.
media.title: Bound for Trouble

media.description: Ash, Tracey and Misty are sailing along on Lapras when they almost crash into another Pokémon trainer wanting to battle Ash.
media.title: Charizard Chills

media.description: Our heroes try, but are unable to extinguish a dangerous fire, until the local fire brigade—a trained team of Wartortles—arrives and squelches the flames.
media.title: The Pokémon Water War

media.description: When a defective Poké Ball prevents Ash from recalling his Snorlax, he and his young friends must somehow heft this Pokémon's slumbering mass over a mountain pass to the nearest Pokémon Center.
media.title: Pokémon Food Fight

media.description: Ash is anxious to square off against the Gym Leader who holds the final badge of the Orange League.
media.title: Pokémon Double Trouble

media.description: Ash and friends are no sooner recruited as assistants in an elaborate project researching Magikarp evolution than Team Rocket surfaces, stealing the object of the young Trainers' research.
media.title: The Wacky Watcher
